==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Past
<hw>Past</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Pass</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a former time or state;
neither present nor future; gone by; elapsed; ended; spent; <as>as,
<ex>past</ex> troubles; <ex>past</ex> offences.</as></def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Past</xex> ages.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Past master</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Master</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Past</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Past
<hw>Past</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A former time or state; a state of
things gone by.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>past</xex>, at least, is
secure.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>D. Webster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The present is only intelligible in the light of the
<qex>past</qex>, often a very remote <qex>past</qex> indeed.</q>
<rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Past</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Past
<hw>Past</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Beyond, in position, or
degree; further than; beyond the reach or influence of.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Who
being <xex>past</xex> feeling.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Eph. iv. 19.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Galled <xex>past</xex> endurance.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Until we be <qex>past</qex> thy borders.</q> <rj><qau>Num. xxi.
22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Love, when once <qex>past</qex> government, is consequently
<qex>past shame</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1050 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Beyond, in time; after; <as>as, <ex>past</ex> the
hour</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is it not <qex>past</qex> two o'clock?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Above; exceeding; more than.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not <qex>past</qex> three quarters of a mile.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bows not <qex>past</qex> three quarters of a yard long.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Past</ent>⟦br⟧

